The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has postponed local government congress to elect one local government national delegate earlier scheduled for today. The national publicity secretary of PDP, Hon Debo Ologunagba, said “A new date for the LGA Congress will be announced in due course. The NWC regrets any inconveniences the postponement may have caused. “All leaders, critical stakeholders and members of our Party across the country should please take note.”